How to create a new repository and modify the repository 

1 - Create the repository on github and add files 

Go to github website and create new repository 
create a folder in your local Mac with the same name then : 

cd /Users/joaopimenta/documents/joaopython/githubscripts/SocialMediaGraphsVis
git init 
git remote add origin https://github.com/silvestrep/SocialMediaGraphsVis.git
git add .
git commit -m "first commit from terminal"
git push origin master

Conclusion: You now have linked your github repository to your local folder and uploaded the files from your folder to github

2 - Go to  your repository Settings -> Github Pages -> master branch -> Save (This will generate your webpage)

3 - Now how to modify and add files to an existing repository 

cd /Users/joaopimenta/documents/joaopython/githubscripts/SocialMediaGraphs
git status 
git add .
git add -u
git commit -m "first commit from terminal"
git push origin master
git log

NOTE: 

DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY ON GITHUB, MAKE CHANGES LOCALLY AND THEN COMMIT TO GITHUB VIA TERMINAL

GOOD DOCUMENTATION WITH DESCRIPTION ON POPULAR GITHUB CODES: https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/basic-git-commands-776639767.html